        <p class="MB_Heading">Wednesday, July 31, 2002</p>
        
        <p class="MB_Submit"><br>
          <span class="MB_SubHead"><a name="335"></a>Patch Message 31st July</span> 
          
          <br>
          Submitted by <a href="mailto:bodi@monkly-business.com">Bodi</a> on 7/31/2002 6:50:36 AM</p>
        <ul>
          <p class="MB_Body"><p>New patch today, in which they have hopefully sorted the bug/loophole that allowed you to type HTML commands in place of normal chat, allowing you to appear to be a GM, a zone wide message or anything else you could think off with different coloured chat. Also it was apparently able to freeze other players by changing font sizes or by typing other HTML commands.

<ul><i><p>We apologize for updating the servers on such short notice. As a bonus, /hitsmode functionality is now available in the new UI. Please check out the context (right-click) menus from New UI Chat windows. Hopefully this version is somewhat easier to understand.  

<p>** General Enhancements and Tweaks **

<p>- NPC and PC names display settings should be saved between sessions. <br>
- Bazaar Search Window is now resizable.<br>
- Disabled Begging and Stealing in the Bazaar<br>
- The New UI Train window no longer cuts off any skill names for INT casters.<br>

<p>- The EverQuest Team</i></ul>

<p>I have also added a new sticky message at the Top of the New Features forum, <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showMessage?topicID=132.topic">New UI Mod Links and Images</a>, in which I would like to create one post with all the UI site links, and your own modifications. Please read the post, and add your links and images (or someone else's with credit) and I will add them to the main site. Thanks!</p>
        </ul>
        
